\v 2 Uba-ke umuntu\x + 3.18; 13.8,9,12. Gal. 6.3. 1 Tim. 6.4.\x* esithi uyazi ulutho, kakazi lutho njengoba kufanele ukuthi azi;
\v 3 kodwa uba umuntu ethanda uNkulunkulu, yena uyaziwa nguye\x + 13.12. Gal. 4.9. Eks. 33.12,17. Nah. 1.7.\x*.
\v 4 Ngakho mayelana lokudla izinto\x + 8.4,7,10. Seb. 15.29.\x* ezihlatshelwe izithombe, siyazi ukuthi isithombe\x + 10.19. Isa. 41.24.\x* kasilutho emhlabeni, lokuthi kakho\x + Dute. 4.35,39. Seb. 14.15. Hlab. 86.10.\x* omunye unkulunkulu ngaphandle koyedwa.
\v 5 Ngoba lanxa kukhona okuthiwa ngonkulunkulu\x + Joha. 10.34.\x*, loba kusezulwini loba kusemhlabeni (njengoba kukhona onkulunkulu abanengi, lamakhosi amanengi),
\v 6 kanti kithi kuloNkulunkulu munye\x + Dute. 4.35,39. Seb. 14.15. Hlab. 86.10.\x*, uBaba\x + Mal. 2.10. Efe. 4.6.\x*, okuvela kuye izinto zonke\x + 11.12. Roma 11.36. Seb. 17.28.\x*, lathi sikuye; leNkosi inye, uJesu Kristu\x + 1.2. Efe. 4.5. Seb. 2.36. Joha. 13.13.\x*, okwa\add vela\add* ngaye konke\x + Joha. 1.3.\x*, lathi si\add khona\add* ngaye.
